newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-INSIGHT - Australian All Ordinaries seen consolidating.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-INSIGHT - Australian All Ordinaries seen consolidating.

text.p: The Australian All Ordinaries share index (Friday close 2355.0) reached the top of its bull channel last week and came off as profit takers entered the market.
Traders are expected to target the lower retracement levels as potential re-entry points while the bull channel holds.
The short term technicals are bullish.
The leading indicators are suggesting a correction and retracement, with the RSI moving sideways and the ROC and Stochastic both heading lower.
Conservative traders are seen waiting until the Stochastic indicators are both below 80, currently at 79/84, before selling.
This could happen as early as the end of business on Monday.
The 1993 high at 2,350, has been broken, and while the index remains above this level, traders are confortable holding long positions.
With higher targets possible, short term traders are likely however, to look at potential retracement levels of 2,350, 2,340 and 2,330 to re-enter the market long.
However, if 2,340 breaks, it will increase the chances that the medium term retarcement will be reached. These are still within the overall bull trend.
In the medium term, the index has broken its resistance, and while it remains above 2,340 traders are keen to remain long.
With four consistent weeks up, traders will become cautious of a retracement and consolidation.
Medium term Fibonacci retarcements are 2,317, 2,297 and 2,277. The latter being the 2nd major medium term support level.
Medium term technicals are sounding a bullish note of caution. The moving average are all bullish, while the leading indicators are moving sideways and in the overbought region.
Traders are generally likely to wait for these latter indicators to move lower, or will be protecting long positions if the index falls below 2,340.

In the longer term, the index is in the overall bull market. 2,350 has been a previous top, and while the index remains above this level traders arewill also be comfortable about holding long positions.
Longer term technicals are bullish. But as with the shorter time frames, a retracement and consolidation is looming.
The index has been in a sound rally, and with all the leading technicals pointing to an overbought situation, traders will most likely introduce profit retention strategies.
It is most likley that the daily Stochastic and the 2,340 level will become significant over the coming week.
A decline through this level is likely to induce some further profit taking.
The index is still however cautiously bullish.
(Daniel Fock is a member of the Australian Technical Analysts Association. Views are his own, not those of Reuters.)
-- Sydney Newsroom 61-2 9373-1812
